  • Method Details

    • setup

      protected void setup()
      Description copied from class: Agent
      This protected method is an empty placeholder for application specific startup code. Agent developers can override it to provide necessary behaviour. When this method is called the agent has been already registered with the Agent Platform AMS and is able to send and receive messages. However, the agent execution model is still sequential and no behaviour scheduling is active yet.

      This method can be used for ordinary startup tasks such as DF registration, but is essential to add at least a Behaviour object to the agent, in order for it to be able to do anything.
